						               													<description>Awards:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-1 Place best solo game in: 8th roll and write design contest.&amp;#10;-1 Place best foreign language game in: 8th roll and write design contest.&amp;#10;-2 Placed best game in: 8th roll and write design contest.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Wargamevault:https://www.wargamevault.com/product/366275/DEAD-ROAD&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dead Road is a survival game in a post-apocalyptic world in which you must survive together with your community, reaching the proposed goals to prosper. In this world you must go to places and find the necessary resources to achieve these goals, but you will meet Zombies on the path that you must eliminate to continue on your way.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dead Road is a single player roll and write survival game.&amp;#10;With a maximum of 40 minutes of play and for people over 10 years old.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Objective&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Reach each goal from levels 1 to 5 by getting the resources necessary for each level. Future expansions will have additional goals that the player must reach to win.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What do you need to play?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     One printed sheet of paper (we recommend putting the sheet in a polypropylene protector).&amp;#10;     One red Dice D-Six to simulate the Horde&amp;rsquo;s moves, both walking and attacking. &amp;#10;     A few Dice D-Six to simulate the survivors.&amp;#10;     Two whiteboard markers. We recommend using a red marker for the March of the Horde and for Morale, and a blue one for the inventory.&amp;#10;     A few tokens or Meeples to simulate the survivors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
